snippet: The growth outlook was further buoyed by other reports showing that in August, factory activity in the mid-Atlantic region hit its highest level since March 2011.
abstract: National Assn of Realtors reports that existing-home sales increased 2.4 percent in July, to an annual rate of 5.15 million units; Labor Department reports that weekly claims for unemployment benefits fell 14,000 to a seasonally adjusted 290,000; figures signal strong economy in the third quarter.
lead_paragraph: The growth outlook was further buoyed by other reports showing that in August, factory activity in the mid-Atlantic region hit its highest level since March 2011.

headline.main: Home and Jobs Data Suggests Momentum
